You can use format {haircut1|haircut2|haircut3} to make your own wildcards. You can also load wildcards from your /ComfyUI/custom_nodes/ComfyUI-Impact-Pack/wildcards/ folder and load them with these nodes. lora loading is disabled as these are used for text only. However if you want to use randomized loras you could connect the model and clips through these to make it work.
These are is added ontop of your face only prompt, but only applies to the face and eye detailers.

When these modules are enabled the workflow will use an gender AI model to detect male or female faces so you don't give your males look male and your females look female.
If your main prompt is a guy you can switch it around with the presets in SEGS Classify nodes.
CFG for individual steps of the workflow

Rescale can add detail to the image, but also changes the output quite a lot. Try for example bypassing it for the first half to only have it effect the final steps of the image. You can bypass them all if you dont want to use it by right clicking and selecting "bypass".
This is your brightness/darkness control. It works in replacement of a offset noise Lora, but you can of course choose to combine them. -1 if full darkness and 1 is full brightness.
Use dimensions to set your resolution :)
You can disable/enable segments of the workflow here.
I urge you to try using different CLIP from different models. If you want the quality from the softcore model on the standard model you could try connecting the model to the first half only

widgets_values:

Check out my cool website: https://donutsdelivery.online/

Checkout my CivitAI: https://civitai.com/user/DonutsDelivery

Discord Invite Link: https://discord.gg/kt2hCJHuKp

You can change the rescale factors for bigger or smaller upscaling. I suggest having them about the same for each upscale pass. 

You can change the start_at_step for denoise%. 25 steps out of 40 is 40% denoise%. Doing it this way makes sure the steps are always set optimally for speed.
